# ROLI — Life Insurance Call Center Analytics Platform

## Business Domain

Life insurance sales operations for Digital Senior Benefits (DSB). All agents operate under a unified flat model (no tier distinctions) on a single Remote (RMT) roster — Charlotte (CHA) is deprecated; historical CHA records remain in `agents` for tenure / historical reporting only. Every agent receives 7 inbound leads/day at $60/lead with supplemental pool access. The platform tracks production, pipeline health, leads pool activity, and contest rankings.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React + Vite + TypeScript, shadcn/ui, Recharts, TailwindCSS
- **Backend**: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Edge Functions in Deno)
- **Scraping**: Apify actors (Playwright) scraping DSB CRM dashboards
- **Automation**: n8n workflows orchestrate scraping, ingestion, and Slack alerts
- **State**: React Context (`DataContext`) for global state, custom hooks per feature

## Key Architecture Patterns

- `DataContext.tsx` is the central data provider — all Supabase queries for daily views flow through `fetchAgentMap`, `refreshDaily`, `refreshPipeline`
- Agent visibility is date-aware: `terminated_date` controls historical inclusion, `is_active` controls scraping
- The `fetchAgentMap` function filters agents based on `selectedDate` vs `terminated_date`
- n8n workflow JSON files in `/n8n` are reference templates — secrets are replaced with `YOUR_*` placeholders before committing
- Apify actor source lives in `/apify/dsb-pipeline-scraper/` — secrets are injected at runtime via actor input

## Critical Data Rules

- All timestamps must be UTC-8 (Pacific) or Central where noted
- Call durations display as MM:SS, never raw seconds
- Missed calls = `lead_uid = 'UNKNOWN'` (not answered_flag)
- Agent capacity: 7 leads/day standard (additional if CR ≥ 15% and pipeline clean)
- `scrape_date` always adjusted to last weekday (no Saturday/Sunday dates)
- CRM agent IDs stored in `agents.crm_agent_id` to bypass fuzzy matching
- Name aliases in `agent_name_aliases` table for CRM name mismatches

## Database Tables

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `agents` | Agent roster with site, crm_agent_id, terminated_date (tier column retained for historical data) |
| `daily_scrape_data` | Daily production metrics from CRM Calls Report |
| `leads_pool_daily_data` | Leads Pool report metrics (separate from main production) |
| `pipeline_compliance_daily` | Pipeline hygiene from CRM Advanced Dashboard Stats |
| `intraday_snapshots` | Hourly snapshots for intraday progression |
| `daily_marketing_summary` | Org-wide CPC/ROAS (synced from Marketing AAR by n8n hourly alert) |
| `agent_name_aliases` | Maps canonical names to CRM dropdown names |
| `evaluation_windows` | Monthly evaluation periods |
| `monthly_snapshots` | ROLI scores per evaluation window |

## File Organization

```
client/src/
  contexts/DataContext.tsx    — Global state provider
  hooks/useAgentTrends.ts     — Day/week/pipeline trend data
  hooks/useDailyPulse.ts      — Daily Pulse page data
  hooks/useAgents.ts          — Agent CRUD + termination
  lib/pipelineIntelligence.ts — Health scores, flags, grades
  lib/exportExcel.ts          — Excel export with date ranges
  pages/DailyPulse.tsx        — Main daily dashboard
  pages/PipelineIntelligence.tsx — Pipeline health dashboard
  pages/AgentTrends.tsx       — Trends with Pipeline tab
  pages/LeadsPool.tsx         — Leads Pool report
  components/AgentDrillDown.tsx — Agent detail modal
```
